INFORMATION WE COLLECT AS A BUSINESS
Personal Information
We collect information that personally identifies, relates to, describes, or is capable of being associated with you (“Personal Information”), including:

Personal Identifiers (e.g., name, birth year, mailing address, email address, phone number, record ID number, political affiliation, voter registration);
Financial Information (e.g., loan type & interest rate, mortgage amount, lender name);
Characteristics of Protected Classifications (e.g., gender, age, ethnic group, language spoken, religion, marital status, sexual orientation, military or veteran status);
Commercial Information (e.g., property location & characteristics, dwelling type, property value, vehicle make/model/year, move-in date, purchase date);
Employment/Professional Information (e.g., occupation);
Health Information (e.g., ailments);
Internet & network information (e.g., browsing history, IP address, data collected by cookies and similar technologies, Site interactions, device information such as device IDs, specifications, and operating system);
Geolocation Data (e.g., latitude & longitude of residence);
Inferences drawn from the above categories of Personal Information that relate to your preferences, characteristics, psychological trends, predispositions, behavior, attitudes, intelligence, abilities, and aptitudes (e.g., value scores, inferred credit scores, net worth models, interests, familial relationships, milestones such as engagement or pregnancy, purchase likelihood models).
The types of Personal Information we collect about you may vary based on how you use the Site and/or Services and your relationship with us.

HOW WE USE AND SHARE INFORMATION AS A BUSINESS
Generally
We use Personal Information for internal purposes, such as to:

Provide you with the Site and Services;
Service our clients’ accounts;
Market our products and services to you;
Perform marketing and other types of data analytics;
Operate information security and anti-fraud programs;
Perform day-to-day business operations; and
Respond to governmental and other legal requests.
Service Providers
We may establish a relationship with other businesses to provide services to us which may include corporate affiliates (“Service Providers”), including for:

Payment processing;
Reporting data usage;
Facilitating marketing and non-marketing communications;
Marketing design and development;
Business analytics (both marketing and non-marketing related);
IT and network administration such as data storage and management, website hosting, and data security;
Professional services such as legal and accounting;
Obtaining legal records;
Collection of accounts; and
Day-to-day business operations such as courier services, facilities management, and document destruction.
We only provide our Service Providers with the information necessary for them to perform these services on our behalf. Each Service Provider is expected to use reasonable security measures appropriate to the nature of the information involved to protect your Personal Information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. Service Providers are prohibited from using Personal Information other than as specified by us.

We share the following types of Personal Information with one or more Service Providers: personal identifiers; financial information; characteristics of protected classifications; commercial information; employment/professional information; health information; geolocation data; inferences drawn from the above categories of Personal Information.

Third-Party Sharing/Selling
We may share or sell your Personal Information with other companies who do not provide services to us (“Third Parties”) such as companies that market and/or sell products and services to consumers and/or businesses and the service providers for those companies. We share or sell the following types of Personal Information with one or more Third Parties: personal identifiers; financial information; characteristics of protected classifications; commercial information; employment/professional information; health information; geolocation data; inferences drawn from the above categories of Personal Information.

