SENSITIVE PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT AS A SERVICE PROVIDER FOR OUR CLIENTS
When acting on behalf of our clients as a service provider, we may collect, use, and disclose information that personally identifies, relates to, describes, or is capable of being associated with you (“Sensitive Personal Information”) for the purpose of servicing those clients. The specific categories of Sensitive Personal Information collected and how that Sensitive Personal Information is used or disclosed is determined by our clients and will vary, and may include:

Personal Identifiers (e.g., name, birth year, mailing address, email address, phone number, record ID number);
Financial Information (e.g., loan type & interest rate, mortgage amount, lender name, login information);
Characteristics of Protected Classifications (e.g., gender, age, ethnic group, language spoken, religion, marital status, sexual orientation, political affiliation);
Commercial Information (e.g., property location & characteristics, dwelling type, property value, vehicle make/model/year, move-in date, purchase date);
Employment/Professional Information (e.g., occupation);
Geolocation Data (e.g., latitude & longitude of residence);
Content of Communications (e.g. mail, email, texts)
Genetic Data
Biometric Data (e.g. Voice recordings, keystroke patterns or rhythms, gait patterns or rhythms, and sleep, health, or exercise data.)
Inferences drawn from the above categories of Personal Information that relate to your preferences, characteristics, psychological trends, predispositions, behavior, attitudes, intelligence, abilities, and aptitudes (e.g., value scores, inferred credit scores, net worth models, interests, familial relationships, milestones such as engagement or pregnancy, purchase likelihood models).
The Sensitive Personal Information collected, used, and disclosed on our clients’ behalf is governed by their privacy policies. When acting on behalf of a client, we supply that client with all information requested by them or consistent with their contract. This information is usually what is required to facilitate a specific transaction or donation but can vary depending on the client. If you request information about the Sensitive Personal Information we collect, use, and disclose on our clients’ behalf, we will direct you to contact the client(s).

